activity_name: District Communication Network (DCN)
activity_description: In order to provide communication services in the country, especially in those areas where no communication services have been provided before, the Ministry of Communications and Information Technology initiated Distract Communication Network (DCN).The main objectives of this project were to provide connections between districts, central and provincial organizations and meanwhile to accelerate and improve the administrative affairs as well as to provide communication services to the people of district and rural areas. This project is mobilized with improved and modern technology that provides (fax, telephone and internet) services.

activity_name: Access to Clinical and Community Maternal, Neonatal, and Women's Health Services (ACCESS)
activity_description: The ACCESS Programs goal is to contribute to the increased use of key maternal health and nutrition interventions through both field-based implementation and global leadership. Specifically, the Program has been charged with responding to the United States Agency for International Developments (USAID) vision of impact on maternal and newborn health through increased use and coverage of maternal/neonatal and womens health and nutrition interventions.
